#lg C	kirugu


@(115-122=c223.C.115) The house of @wSN{Kiš}, @wTN{Ḫursaŋ-kalama}, was destroyed. @wDN{Zababa} took an unfamiliar path away from his beloved dwelling. Mother @wDN{Bau} was lamenting bitterly in her @wTN{E-Iri-kug}. @q[Bau,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly.
$ (1 line fragmentary)
$ (2 lines missing)
@q[,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly.

@(123-132=c223.C.123) @wSN{Kazallu}, the city of teeming multitudes, was cast into confusion. @wDN{Numušda} took an unfamiliar path away from the city, his beloved dwelling. His wife @wDN{Namrat}, the beautiful lady, was lamenting bitterly. @q[Namrat,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. Its river bed was empty, no water flowed. Like a river cursed by @wDN{Enki} its opening channel was dammed up. On the fields fine grains grew no more, people had nothing to eat. The orchards were scorched like an oven, its open country was scattered. The four-legged wild animals did not run about. The four-legged creatures of @wDN{Šakkan} could find no rest.

@(133-142=c223.C.133) @wDN{Lugal-Marda} stepped outside his city. @wDN{Ninzuana} took an unfamiliar path away from her beloved dwelling. @q[Ninzuana,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. @wSN{Isin}, the shrine that was not a quay, was split by onrushing waters. @wDN{Ninisina}, the mother of the Land, wept bitter tears. @q[Ninisina,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. @wDN{Enlil} smote @wTN{Dur-an-ki} with a mace. @wDN{Enlil} made lamentation in his city, the shrine @wSN{Nibru}. Mother @wDN{Ninlil}, the lady of the @wTN{Ki-ur} shrine, wept bitter tears. @q[Ninlil,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly.

@(143-154=c223.C.143) @wSN{Keš}, built all alone on the high open country, was haunted. @wSN{Adab}, the settlement which stretches out along the river,
{was treated as a rebellious land.
} 
{@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} was deprived of water.
}  The snake of the mountains made his lair there, it became a rebellious land. The @wEN{Gutians} bred there, issued their seed. @wDN{Nintur} wept bitter tears over her creatures. @q[Nintur,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. In @wSN{Zabalam} the sacred @wTN{Giguna} was haunted. @wDN{Inana} abandoned @wSN{Unug} and went off to enemy territory. In the @wTN{E-ana} the enemy set eyes upon the sacred Ŋipar shrine. The sacred Ŋipar of @fsux{en} priesthood was defiled. Its @fsux{en} priest was snatched from the Ŋipar and carried off to enemy territory. @q[Inana,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly.


@(155-162=c223.C.155) A violent storm blew over @wSN{Umma} and the @wTN{Šeg-kuršaga}. @wDN{Šara} took an unfamiliar path away from the @wTN{E-maḫ}, his beloved dwelling. @wDN{Ninmul} cried bitter tears over her destroyed city. @q[Ninmul,]{“Oh my city, whose charms can no longer satisfy me,” she cried bitterly. @wSN{Ŋirsu}, the city of heroes, was afflicted with a lightning storm. @wDN{Ninŋirsu} took an unfamiliar path away from the @wTN{E-ninnu}. Mother @wDN{Bau} wept bitter tears in her @wTN{E-Iri-kug}. @q[Bau,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly.

@(163-173=c223.C.163) On that day the word of @wDN{Enlil} was an attacking storm. Who could fathom it? The word of @wDN{Enlil} was destruction on the right, was …… on the left. This is what @wDN{Enlil}, the one who determines destinies, did: @wDN{Enlil} brought down the @wEN{Elamites}, the enemy, from the highlands. @wDN{Nanše}, the noble daughter, was settled outside the city. Fire approached @wDN{Ninmarki} in the shrine @wSN{Gu-aba}. Large boats were carrying off its silver and lapis lazuli. The lady, sacred @wDN{Ninmarki}, was despondent because of her perished goods. On that day he decreed a storm blazing like the mouth of a fire. The province of @wSN{Lagaš} was handed over to @wGN{Elam}. And then the queen also reached the end of her time.

@(174-184=c223.C.174) @wDN{Bau}, as if she were human, also reached the end of her time: @q[Bau,]{“Woe is me! @wDN{Enlil} has handed over the city to the storm. He has handed it over to the storm that destroys cities. He has handed it over to the storm that destroys houses.” @wDN{Dumuzid-abzu} was full of fear in the house of @wSN{Kinirša}. @wSN{Kinirša}, the city to which she belongs, was ordered to be plundered. The city of @wDN{Nanše}, @wSN{Niŋin}, was delivered to the foreigners. @wSN{Sirara}, her beloved dwelling, was handed over to the evil ones. @q[Nance,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. Its sacred Ŋipar of @fsux{en} priesthood was defiled. Its @fsux{en} priest was snatched from the Ŋipar and carried off to enemy territory.

@(185-192=c223.C.185) Mighty strength was set against the banks of the @wWN{Id-nuna-@wDN{Nanna}} canal. The settlements of the @wGN{E-danna} of @wDN{Nanna}, like substantial cattle-pens, were destroyed. Their refugees, like stampeding goats, were chased (?) by dogs. They destroyed @wSN{Gaeš} like milk poured out to dogs, and shattered its finely fashioned statues. @q[,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. Its sacred Ŋipar of @fsux{en} priesthood was defiled. Its @fsux{en} priestess was snatched from the Ŋipar and carried off to enemy territory.

@(193-205=c223.C.193) A lament was raised at the dais that stretches out toward heaven. Its heavenly throne was not set up, was not fit to be crowned (?). It was cut down as if it were a date palm and tied together. @wSN{Aššu}, the settlement that stretches out along the river, was deprived of water. At the place of @wDN{Nanna} where evil had never walked, the enemy walked. How was the house treated thus? The @wTN{E-puḫruma} was emptied. @wSN{Ki-abrig}, which used to be filled with numerous cows and numerous calves, was destroyed like a mighty cattle-pen. @wDN{Ningublaga} took an unfamiliar path away from the @wTN{Ŋa-bura}. @wDN{Ninigara} wept bitter tears all alone. @q[Ninigara,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. Its sacred Ŋipar of @fsux{en} priesthood was defiled. Its @fsux{en} priestess was snatched from the Ŋipar and carried off to enemy territory.

@(206-213=c223.C.206) @wDN{Ninazu} deposited his weapon in a corner in the @wTN{E-gida}. An evil storm swept over @wDN{Ninḫursaŋa} at the @wTN{E-nutura}. Like a pigeon she flew from the window, she stood apart in the open country. @q[Ninḫursaja,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. As for @wSN{Ŋišbanda}, the house filled with lamentation was destroyed among the weeping reeds. @wDN{Ninŋišzida} took an unfamiliar path away from @wSN{Ŋišbanda}. @wDN{Azimua}, the queen of the city, wept bitter tears. @q[Azimua,]{“Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly.

@(214-220=c223.C.214) On that day, the storm forced people to live in darkness. In order to destroy @wSN{Kuara}, it forced people to live in darkness. @wDN{Nineḫama} in her fear wept bitter tears. @q[Ninehama,]{“Alas the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. @wDN{Asarluḫi} put his robes on with haste and ……. @wDN{Lugalbanda} took an unfamiliar path away from his beloved dwelling.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds:} @wDN{Ninsumun} …….
}  @q[Ninsumun,]{“Alas the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly.

@(221-224=c223.C.221) @wSN{Eridug}, floating on great waters, was deprived (?) of drinking water. In its outer environs, which had turned into haunted plains, ……. The loyal man in a place of treachery ……. @wDN{Ka-ḫeŋala} and @wDN{Igi-ḫeŋala} …….

@(225-234=c223.C.225) @q[,]{“I, a young man whom the storm has not destroyed, ……. I, not destroyed by the storm, my attractiveness not brought to an end, ……. We have been struck down like beautiful boxwood trees. We have been struck down like …… with coloured eyes. We have been struck down like statues being cast in moulds. The @wEN{Gutians}, the vandals, are wiping us out. We turned to Father @wDN{Enki} in the @fsux{abzu} of @wSN{Eridug}. …… whatever we shall say, whatever we shall add, …… whatever we shall say, whatever we shall add, we came out from the …… of @wSN{Eridug}.”

@(235-242=c223.C.235) @q[,]{“While were in charge of …… during the day, the shadows ……. While we were in charge of …… during the night, the storm ……. What do we receive trembling on duty during the day? What do we lose not sleeping on duty during the night? @wDN{Enki}, your city has been cursed, it has been given to an enemy land. Why do they reckon us among those who have been displaced from @wSN{Eridug}? Why do they destroy us like palm trees which we have not tended? Why do they break us up like new boats we have not caulked?”


@(243-250=c223.C.243) After @wDN{Enki} had cast his eyes on a foreign land,
$ (1 line unclear)
…… have risen up, have called on their cohorts. @wDN{Enki} took an unfamiliar path away from @wSN{Eridug}. @wDN{Damgalnuna}, the mother of the @wTN{E-maḫ}, wept bitter tears. @q[Damgalnuna,]{“Alas the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. Its sacred Ŋipar of @fsux{en} priesthood was defiled. Its @fsux{en} priestess was snatched from the Ŋipar and carried off to enemy territory.

@(251-259=c223.C.251) In @wSN{Urim} no one went to fetch food, no one went to fetch water. Those who went to fetch food, went away from the food and will not return. Those who went to fetch water, went away from the water and will not return. To the south, the @wEN{Elamites} stepped in, slaughtering ……. In the uplands, the vandals, the enemy, ……. The @wEN{Tidnum} daily strapped the mace to their loins. To the south, the @wEN{Elamites}, like an onrushing wave, were ……. In the uplands, like chaff blowing in the wind, they …… over the open country. @wSN{Urim}, like a great charging wild bull, bowed its neck to the ground.

@(260-271=c223.C.260) This is what @wDN{Enlil}, who decides the fates, did: Again he sent down the @wEN{Elamites}, the enemy, from the mountains. The foremost house, firmly founded, ……. In order to destroy @wSN{Kisiga}, 10 men, even five men ……. Three days and three nights did not pass, …… the city was raked by a hoe. @wDN{Dumuzid} left @wSN{Kisiga} like a prisoner of war, his hands were fettered.
$ (5 lines fragmentary)

@(271-280=c223.C.271) She rode away from her possessions, she went to the mountains. She loudly sang out a lament over those untravelled mountains: @q[Inana,]{“I am queen, but I shall have to ride away from my possessions, and now I shall be a slave in those parts. I shall have to ride away from my silver and lapis lazuli, and now I shall be a slave in those parts. There, slavery, …… people, who can …… it? There, slavery, @wGN{Elam} ……, who can …… it? Alas, the destroyed city, my destroyed house,” she cried bitterly. My queen, though not the enemy, went to enemy land. @wDN{Ama-ušumgal-ana} …… @wSN{Kisiga}. Like a city …….

