#lg G	kirugu


@(360-370=c223.G.360) @wDN{Enlil} then answered his son @wDN{Suen}: @q[Enlil,Suen]{“There is lamentation in the haunted city, reeds of mourning grow there.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} In its midst there is lamentation, reeds of mourning grow there.
}  In its midst the people pass their days in sighing.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} My son, the noble son ……, why do you concern yourself with crying?
}  Oh @wDN{Nanna}, the noble son ……, why do you concern yourself with crying? The judgment uttered by the assembly cannot be reversed. The word of @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} knows no overturning. @wSN{Urim} was indeed given kingship but it was not given an eternal reign. From time immemorial, since the Land was founded, until people multiplied, who has ever seen a reign of kingship that would take precedence for ever? The reign of its kingship had been long indeed but had to exhaust itself. O my @wDN{Nanna}, do not exert yourself in vain, abandon your city.”

@(371-377=c223.G.371) Then my king, the noble son, became distraught. Lord @wDN{Ašimbabbar}, the noble son, grieved. @wDN{Nanna} who loves his city left his city. @wDN{Suen} took an unfamiliar path away from his beloved @wSN{Urim}. In order to go as an exile from her city to foreign territory, @wDN{Ningal} quickly clothed herself and left the city. The @wDN{Anuna} stepped outside of @wSN{Urim}.

@(378-388=c223.G.378) …… approached @wSN{Urim}. The trees of @wSN{Urim} were sick, its reeds were sick. Laments sounded all along its city wall. Daily there was slaughter before it. Large axes were sharpened in front of @wSN{Urim}. The spears, the arms of battle, were prepared. The large bows, throw-sticks and shields gathered together to strike. The barbed arrows covered its outer side like a raining cloud. Large stones fell toegether with great thuds.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} Daily the evil wind returned in the city.
}  @wSN{Urim}, confident in its own strength, stood ready for the murderers. Its people, oppressed by the enemy, could not withstand their weapons.

@(389-402=c223.G.389) In the city, those who had not been felled by weapons succumbed to hunger. Hunger filled the city like water, it would not cease. This hunger contorted people's faces, twisted their muscles. Its people were as if drowning in a pond, they gasped for breath. Its king breathed heavily in his own palace. Its people dropped their weapons, their weapons hit the ground. They struck their necks with their hands and cried. They sought counsel with each other, they searched for clarification: @q[,]{“Alas, what can we say about it? What more can we add to it? How long until we are finished off by this catastrophe? Inside @wSN{Urim} there is death, outside it there is death. Inside it we are to be finished off by famine. Outside it we are to be finished off by @wEN{Elamite} weapons. In @wSN{Urim} the enemy oppresses us, oh, we are finished.”

@(403-410=c223.G.403) The people took refuge (?) behind the city walls. They were united in fear. {The palace that was destroyed by onrushing water was defiled, its doorbolts were torn out} {@noteanchor{1 ms. has instead:} At its main gate the bolts were opened, the storm disloged its door} . @wGN{Elam}, like a swelling flood wave, left (?) only the ghosts. In @wSN{Urim} weapons smashed heads like clay pots. Its refugees were unable to flee, they were trapped inside the walls.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 3 lines:} Like fish living in a pond, they tried to escape. The enemy seized the @wTN{E-kiš-nu-ŋal} of @wDN{Nanna}. They ripped out its heavy …….
}  The statues that were in the shrine were cut down. The great stewardess @wDN{Ninigara} ran away from the storehouse. Its throne was cast down before it, she threw herself down into the dust.


@(411-419=c223.G.411) Its mighty cows with shining horns were captured, their horns were cut off. Its unblemished oxen and grass-fed sheep were slaughtered.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} They were cut down as date palms and were tied together.
}  The palm-trees, strong as mighty copper, the heroic strength, were torn out like rushes, were plucked like rushes, their trunks were turned sideways. Their tops lay in the dust, there was no one to raise them. The midribs of their palm fronds were cut off and their tops were burnt off. Their date spadices that used to fall (?) on the well were torn out. The fertile reeds, which grew in the sacred ……, were defiled. The great tribute that they had collected was hauled off to the mountains.

@(420-434=c223.G.420) The house's great door ornament fell down, its parapet was destroyed. The wild animals that were intertwined on its left and right lay before it like heroes smitten by heroes. Its gaping-mouthed dragons and its awe-inspiring lions were pulled down with ropes like captured wild bulls and carried off to enemy territory. The fragrance of the sacred seat of @wDN{Nanna}, formerly like a fragrant cedar grove, was destroyed.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} Its architrave …… gold and lapis lazuli.
}  The glory of the house, whose glory was once so lovely, was extinguished. Like a storm that fills all the lands, it was built there like twilight in the heavens; its doors adorned with the heavenly stars, its ……. Great bronze latches …… were torn out. Its hinges ……. Together with its door fittings it (?) wept bitterly like a fugitive. The bolt, the holy lock and the great door were not fastened for it. The noise of the door being fastened had ceased; there was no one to fasten it. The …… and was put out in the square.

@(435-448=c223.G.435) The food offerings …… of his royal dining place were altered. In its sacred place (?) the @fsux{tigi}, @fsux{šem} and @fsux{ala} instruments did not sound. Its mighty @fsux{tigi} …… did not perform its sacred song. There was no eloquence in the @wTN{Dubla-maḫ}, the place where oaths used to be taken. The throne was not set up at its place of judgment, justice was not administered. @wDN{Alamuš} threw down his sceptre, his hands trembling. In the sacred bedchamber of @wDN{Nanna} musicians no longer played the @fsux{balaŋ} drum. The sacred box that no one had set eyes upon was seen by the enemy. The divine bed was not set up, it was not spread with clean hay. The statues that were in the shrine were cut down. The cook, the dream interpreter, and the seal keeper did not perform the ceremonies properly. They stood by submissively and were carried off by the foreigners. The priests of the holy @fsux{uzga} shrine and the sacred lustrations, the linen-clad priests, forsook the divine plans and sacred divine powers, they went off to a foreign city.

@(449-459=c223.G.449) In his grief @wDN{Suen} approached his father. He went down on his knee in front of @wDN{Enlil}, the father who begot him: @q[Suen,Enlil]{“O father who begot me, how long will the enemy eye be cast upon my account, how long ……? The lordship and the kingship that you bestowed ……, Father @wDN{Enlil}, the one who advises with just words, the wise words of the Land ……, your inimical judgment ……, look into your darkened heart, terrifying like waves. O Father @wDN{Enlil}, the fate that you have decreed cannot be explained, as for my hairstyle (?) of lordship and the diadem with which I was crowned.” …… he put on a garment of mourning.

@(460-474=c223.G.460) @wDN{Enlil} then provided a favourable response to his son @wDN{Suen}: @q[Enlil,Suen]{“My son, the city built for you in joy and prosperity was given to you as your reign. Destroying the city, overthrowing its great wall and battlements: all this too is part of that reign. …… the black, black days of the reign that has been your lot. As for dwelling in your home, the @wTN{E-temen-ni-guru}, that was properly built -- indeed @wSN{Urim} shall be rebuilt in splendour, the people shall bow down to you. There is to be bounty at its base, there is to be grain. There is to be splendour at its top, the sun shall rejoice there. Let an abundance of grain embrace its table. May @wSN{Urim}, the city whose fate was pronounced by @wDN{An}, be restored for you.” Having pronounced his blessing, @wDN{Enlil} raised his head toward the heavens: @q[Enlil,]{“May the land, south and highland, be organised for @wDN{Nanna}. May the roads of the mountains be set in order for @wDN{Suen}. Like a cloud hugging the earth, they shall submit to him. By order of @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} it shall be conferred.”

@(475-477A=c223.G.475) Father @wDN{Nanna} came into his city of @wSN{Urim} with head raised high. The youth @wDN{Suen} could enter again into the @wTN{E-kiš-nu-ŋal}. @wDN{Ningal} refreshed herself in her sacred living quarters.
{@noteanchor{1 ms. adds 1 line:} In @wSN{Urim} she could enter again into her @wTN{E-kiš-nu-ŋal}.
} 

#trailer rubric	kirugu


@(478=c223.G.478) 4th @fsux{kirugu}.

#lg H	jicgijal


@(479-481=c223.H.479) There is lamentation in the haunted city, mourning reeds grew there. In its midst there is lamentation, mourning reeds grew there. Its people spend their days in moaning.

#trailer rubric	jicgijal


@(482=c223.H.482) @fsux{Ŋišgiŋal}.

#lg I	kirugu


@(483-492=c223.I.483) O bitter storm, retreat, O storm, storm return to your home. O storm that destroys cities, retreat, O storm, storm return to your home. O storm that destroys houses, retreat, O storm, storm return to your home. Indeed the storm that blew on @wGN{Sumer}, blew also on the foreign lands. Indeed the storm that blew on the land, blew on the foreign lands. It has blown on @wGN{Tidnum}, it has blown on the foreign lands. It has blown on @wGN{Gutium}, it has blown on the foreign lands. It has blown on @wGN{Anšan}, it has blown on the foreign lands. It levelled @wGN{Anšan} like a blowing evil wind. Famine has overwhelmed the evildoer; those people will have to submit.

@(493-504=c223.I.493) May @wDN{An} not change the divine powers of heaven, the divine plans for treating the people with justice. May @wDN{An} not change the decisions and judgments to lead the people properly. To travel on the roads of the Land: may @wDN{An} not change it. May @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} not change it, may @wDN{An} not change it. May @wDN{Enki} and @wDN{Ninmaḫ} not change it, may @wDN{An} not change it. That the @wWN{Tigris} and @wWN{Euphrates} should again carry water: may @wDN{An} not change it. That there should be rain in the skies and on the ground speckled barley: may @wDN{An} not change it. That there should be watercourses with water and fields with grain: may @wDN{An} not change it. That the marshes should support fish and fowl: may @wDN{An} not change it. That old reeds and fresh reeds should grow in the reedbeds: may @wDN{An} not change it. May @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} not change it. May @wDN{Enki} and @wDN{Ninmaḫ} not change it.

@(505-518=c223.I.505) That the orchards should bear syrup and grapes, that the high plain should bear the @fsux{mašgurum} tree, that there should be long life in the palace, that the sea should bring forth every abundance: may @wDN{An} not change it. The land densely populated from south to uplands: may @wDN{An} not change it. May @wDN{An} and @wDN{Enlil} not change it, may @wDN{An} not change it. May @wDN{Enki} and @wDN{Ninmaḫ} not change it, may @wDN{An} not change it. That cities should be rebuilt, that people should be numerous, that in the whole universe the people should be cared for; O @wDN{Nanna}, your kingship is sweet, return to your place. May a good abundant reign be long-lasting in @wSN{Urim}. Let its people lie down in safe pastures, let them reproduce. O mankind ……, princess overcome by lamentation and crying! O @wDN{Nanna}! O your city! O your house! O your people!

#trailer rubric	kirugu


@(519=c223.I.519) 5th @fsux{kirugu}.



